cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CYBER, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the use of data mining algorithms for disease prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves classification and comparison of different algorithms, which falls under the category of data mining, making cs.DM (Data Mining) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a tool (Weka) for data analysis, which falls under the category of databases and information retrieval, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the prediction of a disease, which can be considered a cybersecurity issue, making cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) a possible sub-category as well.
